    Package Description
    symposium  
    symposium.model  
  • Classes in symposium.model used by symposium 
    Class and Description
    Constraint
    The class Constraints is an abstract class and the main parent for all constraint classes.
    Panel
    Panel stores information about Panels, such as name, constraints, category, the panel's availability based on the panelists, and messages of the violations a panel might have.
    VenueTime
    VenueTime is used to encapsulate time range information for venues, where each Venue object will have multiple VenueTime objects assigned to it.
  • Classes in symposium.model used by symposium.model 
    Class and Description
    Constraint
    The class Constraints is an abstract class and the main parent for all constraint classes.
    ConstraintPriority
    This class is an enum class which holds the values for Priorities.
    Filter
    Filter Evaluate the given VenueTimes and assign a score to it depending on the filters specification If the filter is REQUIRED, the VenueTimes that do not meet the specifications will be removed from the map.
    NoOverlapConstraint
    The class NoOverlapConstraint is an abstract class which inherits from Constraint.
    Panel
    Panel stores information about Panels, such as name, constraints, category, the panel's availability based on the panelists, and messages of the violations a panel might have.
    Range
    An interface for absolute ranges.
    ScheduleData
    ScheduleData class is the main link between the model and the algorithm.
    TimeConstraint
    The class TimeConstraint is an abstract which inherits from Constraints, @see Constraint for documentation.
    TimeRange
    A single range of absolute time.
    TimeRangeSeries
    A Series of range of absolute time.
    Venue
    Venue stores its own object, its name, size, priority, and VenueTimes
    VenueTime
    VenueTime is used to encapsulate time range information for venues, where each Venue object will have multiple VenueTime objects assigned to it.
